From 4cbe1758714808e3de0914af51e940b15d04caab Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chris Burr <christopher.burr@cern.ch>
Date: Fri, 27 Feb 2026 15:52:52 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] fix: Add extern template declarations to suppress macOS
 visibility warnings

Building ROOT on macOS with -fvisibility-inlines-hidden produces linker
warnings about "direct access to global weak symbol" for template typeinfo.
This occurs when rootcling-generated dictionary code uses typeid() on
templates, creating hidden-visibility references to default-visibility
weak symbols in the source object files.

Adding extern template declarations for explicitly instantiated templates
tells the compiler not to implicitly instantiate the template (and its
typeinfo) in translation units that include the header. Instead, the
linker resolves them from the explicit instantiation in the .cxx file.

Affected templates:
- math/matrix: TMatrixT, TMatrixTSym, TMatrixTBase, TMatrixTSparse,
  TMatrixTLazy and related, TMatrixTUtils classes, TVectorT
- math/mathcore: TKDTree
- graf3d/eve7: REveRecTrackT
- graf3d/eve: TEveRecTrackT
